\subsection{Non-Newtonian fluids}
Some fluids exhibit significant non-Newtonian qualities, as reflected in their constitutive relationship, which describes them. Some categories of non-Newtonian fluids:
\begin{itemize}
\item {\bf Non-constant viscosity:} This is perhaps the simplest way a fluid can be non-Newtonian. Examples include shear thinning fluids {\it e.g.}\ blood, and shear-thickening fluids {\it e.g.}\ fluids containing cornflour, or fluids whose viscosity depends on the temperature of the fluid.
